title.narrative: OUTPUT 2.3: Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) IN SCHOOLS

description.narrative: By 2020, 20,000 boys and 20,000 girls from 200 schools benefit from improved, child-friendly, gender appropriate and inclusive WASH facilities., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, especially the most disadvantaged children, benefit from inclusive, quality early learning and basic education with improved learning outcomes attained.

description.narrative: The UNICEF water sanitation and hygiene in schools (Wins) programme contributed significantly to the education sector response to the COVID-19 emergency by promoting good hygiene and proper handwashing and providing materials such as buckets and tanks for storage of water. The Ministry of Education, Youth and Sport (MoEYS) played an active role in coordinating the rapid provision of Wash supplies required coordinated efforts among stakeholders, the Ministry of Education, Youth and Sport (MoEYS), other development partners as well as national and international NGOs, along with school/local communities | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
